column1: organisation_name
column3: What proportion of patient consultations that healthcare professionals request from other clinical colleagues or specialties are ordered digitally?
column4: What proportion of laboratory tests are requested through a digital order system?
column5: What proportion of radiology tests are requested through a digital order system?
column6: What proportion of requests for any other diagnostic tests are made through a digital order system?
column7: Digital orders are created in a structured format and held as part of the patients electronic health record.
column8: Digital orders are pre-populated with information already collected at the point of care; healthcare professionals do not have re-enter the same information.
column9: When making diagnostic test requests, healthcare professionals have access to department, specialty or organisation level request/order sets.
column10: Healthcare professionals are alerted of duplicate or conflicting test requests
column11: What proportion of patients are positively identified through using barcode technology at the point of sample collection and specimen labelling and prior to all diagnostic tests being performed?
column12: Requests received by diagnostic services are automatically integrated into digital workflows to enable booking, triaging or scheduling.
column13: Healthcare professionals can track the status of requests at all times, including receipt, authorisation, scheduling and completion.
column14: What proportion of laboratory test results are available to healthcare professionals digitally?
column15: What proportion of radiology test results are available to healthcare professionals digitally?
column16: What proportion of results from any other diagnostic tests are available to healthcare professionals digitally?
column17: Healthcare professionals within your organisation have digital access to all relevant diagnostic test results and images for patients under their care, including those undertaken by other providers.
column18: Healthcare professionals have digital access to all relevant diagnostic test results and images for patients under their care, including those undertaken by other local providers.
column19: Digital results are held in a structured format to enable clinical decision support and data extraction.
column20: Healthcare professionals are automatically alerted of all results that require acknowledgement and an audit Â trail exists to demonstrate the acknowledgement process and actions taken.
column21: Healthcare professionals can digitally access diagnostic test results and images quickly and easily at the point of care
